        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:57PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Greenwood, or 13 miles south of Hornell, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Troupsburg, Coopers Plains, Greenwood, Addison, Campbell, Woodhull,
Young Hickory, Cameron, Lindley, and Jasper.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
